1
00:01:02,903 --> 00:01:06,239
ENGLAND 1554

2
00:01:08,701 --> 00:01:11,703
HENRY VIII IS DEAD

3
00:01:12,788 --> 00:01:14,664
THE COUNTRY IS DIVIDED...

4
00:01:14,957 --> 00:01:16,249
... IN CATHOLICS ANd PROTESTANTS

5
00:01:16,792 --> 00:01:20,670
HENRY'S OLDEST DOCHTER MARY,
A DEVOUT CATHOLIC, IS QUEEN

6
00:01:21,171 --> 00:01:23,256
SHE IS WITHOUT CHILDREN

7
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:28,719
THE GREATEST FEAR OF THE CATHOLICS IS THAT SHE
WILL BE SUCCEEDED BY HER PROTESTANT HALF-SISTER

8
00:01:35,518 --> 00:01:36,727
I praise the LORD

9
00:01:38,131 --> 00:01:41,167
and so shall be saved
from mine enemies !

10
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:46,304
The waves of death
have closed about me !

11
00:01:47,181 --> 00:01:50,799
The cords of hell
have encompassed me about

12
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:55,392
and the snares of death
have overtaken me !

13
00:01:56,106 --> 00:01:59,190
The cords of hell
have encompassed me about

14
00:01:59,693 --> 00:02:04,319
and the snares of death
have overtaken me !

15
00:02:04,447 --> 00:02:10,816
In my tribulation I call to the Lord
and cry to my God

16
00:02:10,953 --> 00:02:15,032
and He heard my voice
cry out His temple ... !

17
00:02:15,124 --> 00:02:17,579
Move back ! Clear the way !

18
00:02:17,918 --> 00:02:19,957
Move back !

19
00:02:22,339 --> 00:02:24,378
Keep in line, woman !

20
00:02:30,681 --> 00:02:35,841
By order of their gracious Majesties,
Queen Mary and King Philip,

21
00:02:35,936 --> 00:02:40,846
we are come to witness the burning
of these Protestant heretics

22
00:02:40,940 --> 00:02:46,147
who have denied the authority
of the one true Catholic church

23
00:02:46,237 --> 00:02:49,107
and of His Holiness the Pope.

24
00:02:50,241 --> 00:02:55,401
Let them burn for all eternity
in the flames of hell.

25
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:06,334
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

26
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:12,213
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

27
00:03:13,513 --> 00:03:18,933
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

28
00:03:19,018 --> 00:03:21,140
God bless you, Master Ridley !

29
00:03:21,229 --> 00:03:25,143
For the love of God, friends, help me !
I burn too slowly !

30
00:03:26,859 --> 00:03:30,607
Help them !
For God's sake, help them !

31
00:04:33,839 --> 00:04:36,626
Your Grace, the Queen is with child.

32
00:04:36,717 --> 00:04:41,509
They should've consulted me
before they rang the bells.

33
00:04:45,225 --> 00:04:47,264
Is it true ?

34
00:04:47,352 --> 00:04:52,808
She has ceased to bleed, her breasts have
some milk, and her stomach is swollen.

35
00:04:52,899 --> 00:04:54,227
Is it true ?

36
00:04:54,317 --> 00:04:58,777
The King has not shared her bed
for many months.

37
00:04:58,863 --> 00:05:02,942
He has a repugnance for it,
as lately Your Grace has for mine.

38
00:05:23,261 --> 00:05:24,885
Norfolk...

39
00:05:25,889 --> 00:05:29,174
Your Majesties,
this is most wondrous news.

40
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,761
Indeed.

41
00:05:30,852 --> 00:05:35,430
We do thank God for this,
our most happy condition.

42
00:05:35,523 --> 00:05:38,060
We must also thank His Majesty
for this event

43
00:05:38,150 --> 00:05:40,640
which is nothing short of a miracle.

44
00:05:44,156 --> 00:05:48,616
What news, my Lords,
of the rebellion against our authority ?

45
00:05:49,703 --> 00:05:51,327
Sussex ?

46
00:05:51,413 --> 00:05:54,828
Madam, it is safely dispatched,
thanks to His Grace.

47
00:05:54,916 --> 00:05:58,830
Sir Thomas Wyatt and the other leaders
are already dealt with.

48
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:02,999
If they had succeeded,
these Protestants and heretics

49
00:06:03,091 --> 00:06:05,166
meant to place your sister

50
00:06:05,259 --> 00:06:07,381
upon the throne.

51
00:06:08,888 --> 00:06:12,387
There is no proof
against the Lady Elizabeth.

52
00:06:12,474 --> 00:06:16,008
- She is plainly guilty.
- What need is there of proof ?

53
00:06:16,103 --> 00:06:19,187
If she remains alive,
there will be plots to raise her

54
00:06:19,273 --> 00:06:20,980
to the throne.

55
00:06:21,066 --> 00:06:22,061
Ambassador ?

56
00:06:26,363 --> 00:06:28,402
I agree with His Grace.

57
00:06:28,490 --> 00:06:32,736
She is a heretic.
She must never be allowed to succeed.

58
00:06:32,827 --> 00:06:34,155
But if she...

59
00:06:35,246 --> 00:06:38,199
If she were brought properly to trial,

60
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:40,912
she would not be found guilty,

61
00:06:41,002 --> 00:06:43,872
and we would be condemned.
She has friends in Parliament.

62
00:06:43,963 --> 00:06:47,627
My sister was born
of that whore Anne Boleyn !

63
00:06:47,716 --> 00:06:51,630
She was born a bastard !
She will never rule England !

64
00:06:59,352 --> 00:07:04,642
Your Grace will find some proof
of her treachery. I am most sure of it.

65
00:07:46,022 --> 00:07:47,646
It was so fast !

66
00:08:02,496 --> 00:08:04,535
May I join you, my Lady ?

67
00:08:13,756 --> 00:08:15,795
If it please you, sir.

68
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:34,200
My Lady !

69
00:09:34,291 --> 00:09:35,701
My Lady !

70
00:09:46,136 --> 00:09:47,760
Princess Elizabeth !

71
00:10:02,359 --> 00:10:04,398
Princess Elizabeth !

72
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:14,778
You are accused of conspiring
with Sir Thomas Wyatt

73
00:10:14,871 --> 00:10:17,540
against Her Sovereign Majesty

74
00:10:17,624 --> 00:10:20,293
and are arrested for treason.

75
00:10:20,376 --> 00:10:25,962
I am commanded to take you hence
from this place... to the Tower.

76
00:10:39,436 --> 00:10:41,475
Remember who you are.

77
00:10:50,405 --> 00:10:52,444
Do not be afraid of them.

78
00:10:56,828 --> 00:10:58,867
My Lady.

79
00:11:38,909 --> 00:11:40,948
Prisoner to the steps.

80
00:11:48,877 --> 00:11:52,625
I cannot confess to something
I did not do.

81
00:11:52,714 --> 00:11:54,124
Your denials are in vain.

82
00:11:54,216 --> 00:11:58,545
You knew of the rebellion, Madam.
It is plain enough.

83
00:11:58,636 --> 00:12:00,379
Where is your proof ?

84
00:12:00,472 --> 00:12:02,594
It was to your advantage.

85
00:12:02,682 --> 00:12:04,721
You must let me see the Queen...

86
00:12:04,809 --> 00:12:08,058
You despise the Queen,
and the Catholic faith.

87
00:12:15,736 --> 00:12:19,567
I am a true and faithful subject.

88
00:12:20,824 --> 00:12:22,448
I attend Mass...

89
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:25,071
You pretend ! But in your heart...

90
00:12:27,205 --> 00:12:30,988
What's that ? What say you, Madam ?

91
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,791
Speak up !

92
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:37,170
Madam, if there is some small truth
in these charges,

93
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,874
however innocently or unknowingly
you did proceed,

94
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:43,007
you had best confess.

95
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,838
I ask you

96
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:49,757
why we must tear ourselves apart
for this small question of religion.

97
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:51,927
Catholic, Protestant... !

98
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:55,969
You think it small,
though it killed your mother !

99
00:13:06,075 --> 00:13:07,699
We all...

100
00:13:09,871 --> 00:13:12,540
We all believe in God, my Lords.

101
00:13:12,623 --> 00:13:16,572
No, Madam,
there is only one true belief.

102
00:13:16,669 --> 00:13:18,827
The other - heresy.

103
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:49,779
Madam, you are cold.

104
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:52,404
I do not need your pity.

105
00:13:52,703 --> 00:13:54,695
Accept it, then,

106
00:13:54,788 --> 00:13:56,365
for my sake.

107
00:13:59,793 --> 00:14:01,619
Thank you.

108
00:14:02,754 --> 00:14:05,423
I shall not forget this kindness.

109
00:15:17,325 --> 00:15:19,566
Tonight I think I die.

110
00:15:26,751 --> 00:15:28,790
Madam.

111
00:15:31,547 --> 00:15:33,290
No... !

112
00:15:45,977 --> 00:15:48,265
Save me ! Save me !

113
00:16:22,512 --> 00:16:26,094
I am Your Majesty's most humble servant.

114
00:16:42,031 --> 00:16:43,904
Come here.

115
00:16:45,117 --> 00:16:47,786
Closer, so I might see your face.

116
00:16:55,668 --> 00:16:59,167
When I look at you
I see nothing of the King.

117
00:16:59,255 --> 00:17:02,172
Only that whore - your mother.

118
00:17:04,218 --> 00:17:09,425
My father never did anything so well
as to cut off her head.

119
00:17:09,515 --> 00:17:12,634
Your Majesty forgets
he was also my father.

120
00:17:16,021 --> 00:17:19,852
Why will you not confess
your crimes against me ?

121
00:17:19,941 --> 00:17:23,190
Because, Your Majesty,
I have committed none.

122
00:17:25,697 --> 00:17:28,366
You speak with such sincerity !

123
00:17:28,783 --> 00:17:32,317
I see you are still a consummate actress.

124
00:17:34,747 --> 00:17:37,035
My husband is gone.

125
00:17:37,124 --> 00:17:39,793
They have poisoned my child.

126
00:17:41,212 --> 00:17:43,667
They say it is a tumour.

127
00:17:45,382 --> 00:17:47,421
Madam, you are not well.

128
00:17:47,509 --> 00:17:51,636
They say this cancer
will make you Queen, but they are wrong !

129
00:17:51,722 --> 00:17:56,182
Look there ! It is your death warrant.
All I need do is sign it.

130
00:17:56,268 --> 00:18:01,724
Mary, if you sign that paper,
you will be murdering your own sister.

131
00:18:07,445 --> 00:18:10,114
You will promise me something ?

132
00:18:12,617 --> 00:18:16,744
When I am gone, you will
do everything in your power

133
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:19,154
to uphold the Catholic faith.

134
00:18:19,248 --> 00:18:25,451
Do not take away from the people
the consolations of the Blessed Virgin.

135
00:18:28,715 --> 00:18:30,754
When I am Queen

136
00:18:31,301 --> 00:18:33,340
I promise

137
00:18:36,055 --> 00:18:38,925
to act as my conscience dictates.

138
00:18:41,519 --> 00:18:43,844
Well, do not think to be Queen at all.

139
00:18:43,938 --> 00:18:47,271
You may return to your house at Hatfield,

140
00:18:47,358 --> 00:18:50,773
but you will remain under arrest
until I am recovered.

141
00:18:52,613 --> 00:18:54,652
Thank you, Your Majesty.

142
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:56,150
No...

143
00:18:56,241 --> 00:19:01,317
Feed her to the wolves.
Let her see what they are like.

144
00:19:47,915 --> 00:19:52,042
She is just a child,
and yet still you piss yourselves !

145
00:19:55,464 --> 00:19:58,583
Your Grace,
Protestants are returning from abroad.

146
00:19:58,676 --> 00:20:03,836
Yes, and have made plans to massacre
every Catholic in England.

147
00:20:04,264 --> 00:20:08,510
There would be butchery indeed
if such a plan were even conceivable.

148
00:20:08,602 --> 00:20:10,974
They say Walsingham
will return from France.

149
00:20:11,062 --> 00:20:13,101
Walsingham is nothing !

150
00:20:20,613 --> 00:20:22,819
Be sure he does not.

151
00:20:22,907 --> 00:20:27,734
There is so little beauty in this world,
and so much suffering.

152
00:20:29,705 --> 00:20:32,789
Do you suppose
that is what God had in mind ?

153
00:20:33,917 --> 00:20:36,787
That is to say, if there is a God at all.

154
00:20:38,964 --> 00:20:42,213
Perhaps there is nothing
in this universe but ourselves

155
00:20:43,218 --> 00:20:45,257
and our thoughts.

156
00:20:52,727 --> 00:20:54,766
Think before you do this.

157
00:21:04,446 --> 00:21:06,853
If you must do it,

158
00:21:06,949 --> 00:21:08,988
then do it now.

159
00:21:10,202 --> 00:21:12,490
And without regret.

160
00:21:12,579 --> 00:21:14,737
But first think carefully

161
00:21:18,251 --> 00:21:20,290
and be certain

162
00:21:20,462 --> 00:21:22,501
why it needs to be done.

163
00:21:29,929 --> 00:21:31,968
Come here.

164
00:21:42,566 --> 00:21:44,605
Look out there.

165
00:21:45,861 --> 00:21:48,530
There is a whole world waiting for you.

166
00:21:50,532 --> 00:21:54,659
Innocence
is the most precious thing you possess.

167
00:21:55,578 --> 00:21:58,662
Lose that and you lose your soul.

168
00:22:14,429 --> 00:22:15,887
..et Spiritus Sancti...

169
00:22:15,973 --> 00:22:17,087
Amen.

170
00:22:17,182 --> 00:22:18,806
Father...

171
00:22:18,892 --> 00:22:21,429
- Sir William !
- My Lady...

172
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:24,805
There was nowhere else
we could meet in safety.

173
00:22:24,898 --> 00:22:27,139
Listen to me carefully.

174
00:22:27,233 --> 00:22:29,558
All things move in our favour.

175
00:22:29,652 --> 00:22:33,186
Many of our friends
are returning from exile.

176
00:22:33,281 --> 00:22:36,649
But these are most uncertain times

177
00:22:36,742 --> 00:22:39,067
and your life remains in danger.

178
00:22:39,161 --> 00:22:41,734
You must therefore say nothing

179
00:22:41,830 --> 00:22:45,530
and meet no-one
whose visit may compromise you.

180
00:22:45,626 --> 00:22:46,906
No-one ?

181
00:22:47,002 --> 00:22:49,872
No-one. Not even Lord Robert.

182
00:22:49,963 --> 00:22:55,502
- But he is a trusted friend.
- Child, listen to me. Please.

183
00:22:55,594 --> 00:22:59,638
You are most innocent
in the ways of this world

184
00:22:59,722 --> 00:23:01,797
and we must do all we may

185
00:23:01,891 --> 00:23:05,010
to guarantee the security of your throne.

186
00:23:05,103 --> 00:23:08,222
Now there is someone
I do wish you to meet.

187
00:23:08,314 --> 00:23:11,599
Monseigneur Alvaro de la Quadra,
the Spanish Ambassador.

188
00:23:11,692 --> 00:23:12,723
Why do l...

189
00:23:16,947 --> 00:23:18,773
My Lady,

190
00:23:18,866 --> 00:23:22,032
I bring a message.

191
00:23:22,119 --> 00:23:27,113
The King of Spain is enraptured,
and offers you his hand in marriage.

192
00:23:27,207 --> 00:23:29,697
My sister is not yet dead.

193
00:23:29,793 --> 00:23:32,034
Her bed is still warm.

194
00:23:32,629 --> 00:23:35,499
His Majesty finds it already cold.

195
00:23:48,477 --> 00:23:50,516
You must sign it.

196
00:23:50,604 --> 00:23:53,889
For the love of God, sign it.

197
00:23:57,235 --> 00:24:00,319
Will you leave your kingdom to a heretic ?

198
00:24:06,870 --> 00:24:10,914
He then said that this King
would marry me

199
00:24:10,998 --> 00:24:15,576
but would not expect to share my bed
more than two or three times a year.

200
00:24:15,670 --> 00:24:17,329
As much as that ?

201
00:24:20,507 --> 00:24:22,166
Well, he...

202
00:24:22,259 --> 00:24:24,132
He is enraptured.

203
00:24:24,219 --> 00:24:25,214
Naturally.

204
00:24:27,723 --> 00:24:31,672
But... his affairs would otherwise
keep him in Spain.

205
00:24:33,395 --> 00:24:35,636
Then the King is a fool.

206
00:24:39,484 --> 00:24:43,611
What could ever be important enough
to keep him from your bed ?

207
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:55,700
Robert,

208
00:24:55,791 --> 00:24:58,163
you should not say such things.

209
00:24:58,252 --> 00:25:00,291
Then I shall only think them.

210
00:25:04,508 --> 00:25:10,343
Everything is so uncertain !
Sir William says my life is still in danger.

211
00:25:10,430 --> 00:25:14,094
Do not listen to everything he tells you.
Do not listen to any of them.

212
00:25:14,183 --> 00:25:15,890
None of them are of consequence.

213
00:25:15,977 --> 00:25:20,056
- When you are Queen...
- I am not... I am not Queen yet.

214
00:25:20,147 --> 00:25:22,104
You will be.

215
00:25:22,191 --> 00:25:23,898
Elizabeth,

216
00:25:23,984 --> 00:25:25,941
Queen of England.

217
00:25:27,071 --> 00:25:29,478
A court to worship you.

218
00:25:29,573 --> 00:25:31,648
A country to obey you.

219
00:25:31,742 --> 00:25:34,659
Poems written celebrating your beauty.

220
00:25:34,745 --> 00:25:39,406
Music composed in your honour,
and they will be nothing to you.

221
00:25:40,292 --> 00:25:42,331
I will mean nothing to you.

222
00:25:47,465 --> 00:25:50,002
How could you ever be nothing to me ?

223
00:25:53,221 --> 00:25:56,305
Robert, you know
you are everything to me.

224
00:25:57,099 --> 00:25:59,138
All that I am

225
00:25:59,226 --> 00:26:01,265
it is you.

226
00:26:07,776 --> 00:26:08,060
Benedicta tu in mulieribus

227
00:26:10,028 --> 00:26:14,155
et benedictus fructus ventris tui, lesus.

228
00:26:15,075 --> 00:26:17,114
Sancta Maria, Mater Dei

229
00:26:18,244 --> 00:26:21,328
ora pro nobis peccatoribus, nunc...

230
00:26:25,877 --> 00:26:27,916
Is she dead ?

231
00:26:47,355 --> 00:26:49,394
Give it to her.

232
00:27:15,924 --> 00:27:17,501
My Lady...

233
00:27:21,554 --> 00:27:24,009
The Earl of Sussex is here.

234
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:17,269
The Queen is dead !

235
00:28:17,733 --> 00:28:19,772
Long live the Queen !

236
00:28:22,571 --> 00:28:24,777
Long live the Queen !

237
00:28:32,413 --> 00:28:34,738
This is the Lord's doing

238
00:28:36,584 --> 00:28:42,372
and it is marvellous in our eyes.

239
00:28:45,592 --> 00:28:48,545
To the north, I present unto you

240
00:28:48,637 --> 00:28:51,673
Elizabeth, your undoubted Queen !

241
00:28:54,184 --> 00:28:56,425
To the south, I present to you

242
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:59,390
Elizabeth, your undoubted Queen !

243
00:30:16,804 --> 00:30:18,843
I crown thee Elizabeth,

244
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:24,800
Queen of England, lreland and France.

245
00:30:57,343 --> 00:30:59,798
God save Your Majesty.

246
00:31:04,516 --> 00:31:10,269
Your Majesty has inherited
a most parlous and degenerate state.

247
00:31:10,355 --> 00:31:13,854
It's threatened from abroad
by France and Spain

248
00:31:13,942 --> 00:31:17,393
and is weaker in men, monies and riches

249
00:31:17,487 --> 00:31:19,444
than I have ever known it.

250
00:31:19,530 --> 00:31:21,024
What are you saying ?

251
00:31:21,115 --> 00:31:25,444
Madam, your treasury is empty.
The Navy is run-down,

252
00:31:25,536 --> 00:31:28,821
there is no standing army,
and no munitions.

253
00:31:28,914 --> 00:31:33,243
There is not a fortress
that could withstand a single shot.

254
00:31:33,335 --> 00:31:37,249
- I have no desire for war, sir.
- But that is not the end of it.

255
00:31:37,339 --> 00:31:41,087
Here at home there are those
who wish Your Majesty ill.

256
00:31:41,176 --> 00:31:45,339
Mary of Scots has already
laid claim to your throne,

257
00:31:45,430 --> 00:31:47,339
and Norfolk...

258
00:31:47,432 --> 00:31:50,432
Norfolk covets it relentlessly.

259
00:31:50,518 --> 00:31:55,060
Madam, until you marry
and produce an heir,

260
00:31:55,940 --> 00:31:58,609
you will find no security.

261
00:32:13,623 --> 00:32:15,662
That's Sir Christopher Hatton.

262
00:32:27,762 --> 00:32:30,003
- There is Sir William Makepeace...
- I do not see...

263
00:32:30,097 --> 00:32:31,555
- Lord Ensley, Your Majesty.
- Delighted.

264
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:35,174
I do not see why a woman
need marry at all.

265
00:32:48,907 --> 00:32:51,195
Come on, come on !

266
00:32:52,452 --> 00:32:54,491
This is Mistress Quickly.

267
00:33:10,260 --> 00:33:14,257
You will recall His Excellency
the Spanish Ambassador.

268
00:33:14,348 --> 00:33:16,387
How could I forget ?

269
00:33:16,475 --> 00:33:17,470
Excellency.

270
00:33:17,559 --> 00:33:19,598
Your Majesty.

271
00:33:23,982 --> 00:33:25,725
He's French. You'll have to speak up.

272
00:33:34,742 --> 00:33:36,781
Do I know that gentleman ?

273
00:33:37,328 --> 00:33:42,203
That is Sir Francis Walsingham, Madam.
He has returned from exile

274
00:33:42,291 --> 00:33:46,703
and I have appointed him
to have a care for Your Majesty's person.

275
00:33:53,885 --> 00:33:55,711
Ah !

276
00:33:56,012 --> 00:33:57,589
Excellency...

277
00:33:59,140 --> 00:34:00,135
Majesty...

278
00:34:06,355 --> 00:34:11,597
May I present the French Ambassador,
His Excellency Monsieur de Foix.

279
00:34:11,694 --> 00:34:13,485
Your Excellency.

280
00:34:15,197 --> 00:34:19,324
I suppose the French
do offer some suitor to her.

281
00:34:19,409 --> 00:34:21,318
Naturally.

282
00:34:21,411 --> 00:34:25,408
Everything now depends
upon the husband that woman takes.

283
00:34:25,499 --> 00:34:27,657
King Henry of Anjou
sends you brotherly love.

284
00:34:27,751 --> 00:34:33,539
He trusts the relationship between
our countries may be much improved.

285
00:34:33,631 --> 00:34:35,006
That is also my hope.

286
00:34:35,091 --> 00:34:40,048
The King expects that you will
consider the suit of his brother,

287
00:34:40,137 --> 00:34:42,627
the Duke of Anjou.

288
00:34:42,723 --> 00:34:46,554
Her Majesty will consider
the proposal most carefully.

289
00:34:49,897 --> 00:34:54,724
It is unfortunate, however,
that the Duke's aunt, Mary of Guise,

290
00:34:54,818 --> 00:34:58,352
chooses to garrison Scotland
with French troops.

291
00:35:02,367 --> 00:35:03,777
Ladies...

292
00:35:08,122 --> 00:35:13,827
The marriage of a Queen, Excellency,
is born of politics, not childish passion.

293
00:35:22,469 --> 00:35:23,631
Your Grace.

294
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:25,760
Walsingham !

295
00:35:28,558 --> 00:35:30,597
Welcome to England.

296
00:35:30,685 --> 00:35:33,472
- Your Grace is surprised ?
- No.

297
00:35:33,563 --> 00:35:35,638
Only a little disappointed.

298
00:36:20,566 --> 00:36:22,605
Play a volta !

299
00:37:16,828 --> 00:37:19,662
When may I see you in private ?

300
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,119
In private ?

301
00:37:23,709 --> 00:37:25,748
Have you forgot, my Lord ?

302
00:37:27,046 --> 00:37:28,872
I am Queen now.

303
00:37:48,441 --> 00:37:49,816
He's coming.

304
00:37:49,901 --> 00:37:51,063
He's coming !

305
00:38:04,498 --> 00:38:06,490
My Ladies.

306
00:38:06,583 --> 00:38:08,622
My Lord.

307
00:38:10,712 --> 00:38:13,915
You blush, Lady Knollys.

308
00:38:14,007 --> 00:38:16,213
Are you in love ?

309
00:38:16,301 --> 00:38:17,960
No, my Lord.

310
00:38:18,053 --> 00:38:21,137
Then you should be,
or waste all that beauty.

311
00:38:30,606 --> 00:38:32,645
Does Her Majesty sleep ?

312
00:38:33,317 --> 00:38:35,356
Not yet, Sir William.

313
00:38:35,444 --> 00:38:37,685
She is... overwrought.

314
00:38:38,781 --> 00:38:41,865
Show me Her Majesty's sheets
every morning.

315
00:38:41,950 --> 00:38:47,110
- I must know all her proper functions.
- Proper functions, Sir William ?

316
00:38:47,205 --> 00:38:49,244
Indeed.

317
00:38:51,418 --> 00:38:56,756
Her Majesty's body and person
are no longer her own property.

318
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,962
They belong to the State.

319
00:38:59,050 --> 00:39:01,089
Yes, Sir William.

320
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:51,858
Your Grace.

321
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:54,321
Your Grace, Her Majesty has not risen.

322
00:40:54,409 --> 00:40:56,235
Your Grace !

323
00:40:56,787 --> 00:41:01,247
Please ! Your Grace ! Her Majesty
is not yet ready to receive visitors.

324
00:41:01,333 --> 00:41:03,159
Madam !

325
00:41:05,879 --> 00:41:09,164
You had best get up.
There is some grave news.

326
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:16,509
My Lady, I'm sorry...

327
00:41:16,597 --> 00:41:21,389
Mary of Guise has increased the French
garrison in Scotland by 4,000 men.

328
00:41:21,477 --> 00:41:23,967
Perhaps more.

329
00:41:24,063 --> 00:41:25,605
Madam...

330
00:41:25,689 --> 00:41:30,231
I'm afraid the French mean to attack
while we are still weak

331
00:41:30,319 --> 00:41:33,901
and while Your Majesty's reign
is still uncertain.

332
00:41:36,950 --> 00:41:38,989
What is your counsel ?

333
00:41:39,077 --> 00:41:43,904
Madam, we must with all haste
raise an army to march upon Scotland.

334
00:41:48,711 --> 00:41:50,750
Can... can... ?

335
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,839
Can we not send emissaries ?

336
00:41:56,927 --> 00:42:01,304
There is no time for that !
As Queen we look to you for action,

337
00:42:01,390 --> 00:42:07,309
unless you are content to wait for the
French to send more reinforcements.

338
00:42:07,395 --> 00:42:08,853
Here.

339
00:42:23,744 --> 00:42:25,783
Are you all in agreement ?

340
00:42:25,871 --> 00:42:30,912
I say there has never been a better time
to abate the French pride.

341
00:42:31,001 --> 00:42:31,996
Arundel ?

342
00:42:32,961 --> 00:42:37,088
War is a sin,
but sometimes a necessary one.

343
00:42:40,886 --> 00:42:46,046
Lord Robert, you were appointed to the
Council to protect England's interests.

344
00:42:46,141 --> 00:42:49,225
Now it appears
you do not have the stomach for it.

345
00:42:49,310 --> 00:42:51,136
I am in agreement, Your Grace,

346
00:42:51,229 --> 00:42:56,021
ifYour Majesty's throne is at risk.

347
00:43:03,657 --> 00:43:06,990
- What say you, Walsingham ?
- Your Majesty !

348
00:43:07,077 --> 00:43:10,410
I say a prince should rather
be slow to take action

349
00:43:10,497 --> 00:43:16,083
and should watch that he does not
come to be afraid of his own shadow.

350
00:43:16,169 --> 00:43:20,462
You are not, Sir Francis,
a member of Council,

351
00:43:20,548 --> 00:43:22,540
nor are you in the majority.

352
00:43:24,552 --> 00:43:26,591
I do not like wars.

353
00:43:27,930 --> 00:43:30,385
They have uncertain outcomes.

354
00:45:17,201 --> 00:45:21,198
SCOTLAND

355
00:45:53,235 --> 00:45:54,610
Stop !

356
00:46:29,436 --> 00:46:31,677
Go back to England,

357
00:46:31,771 --> 00:46:34,261
and take this to your Queen.

358
00:46:36,568 --> 00:46:39,438
English blood on French colours.

359
00:46:40,697 --> 00:46:43,614
Send him back to his Queen

360
00:46:43,699 --> 00:46:48,325
and make sure he remains alive.

361
00:46:50,289 --> 00:46:55,531
Tell that bastard Queen not to send
children to fight Mary of Guise !

362
00:47:05,720 --> 00:47:09,135
- Where are my councillors ?
- I know not, Madam.

363
00:47:09,224 --> 00:47:13,802
- Where is Lord Robert ?
- Lord Robert, Madam, has gone hunting.

364
00:47:18,608 --> 00:47:20,647
Leave me.

365
00:47:20,735 --> 00:47:22,774
Go ! Go !

366
00:47:26,865 --> 00:47:31,775
I regret to inform Your Majesty
of our miserable defeat in Scotland.

367
00:47:31,870 --> 00:47:35,155
The Bishops still demand
Your Majesty's removal.

368
00:47:35,248 --> 00:47:38,248
They find support in every quarter.

369
00:47:39,461 --> 00:47:43,161
Alas, Madam,
we are come already to catastrophe.

370
00:48:17,247 --> 00:48:20,117
How dare you come into my presence !

371
00:48:23,169 --> 00:48:25,208
Why do you follow me here ?

372
00:48:25,296 --> 00:48:28,795
It is my business
to protect Your Majesty

373
00:48:30,134 --> 00:48:32,173
against all things.

374
00:48:32,261 --> 00:48:36,305
I do not need protection.
I need to be left alone !

375
00:48:36,390 --> 00:48:38,429
Majesty...

376
00:48:39,434 --> 00:48:43,016
They should never have been
sent to Scotland.

377
00:48:45,357 --> 00:48:48,856
My father would not have made
such a mistake.

378
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,893
I have been proved unfit to rule.

379
00:48:54,449 --> 00:48:58,576
That is what you all think,
is it not, Walsingham ?

380
00:48:58,661 --> 00:49:00,653
It is not for me to judge you.

381
00:49:03,457 --> 00:49:08,795
Why did they send children ! Why
did they not send proper reinforcements !

382
00:49:08,879 --> 00:49:11,548
The Bishops would not let them.

383
00:49:11,632 --> 00:49:14,835
They spoke against it in the pulpits.

384
00:49:14,926 --> 00:49:19,255
Then... they are speaking
against their Queen.

385
00:49:19,347 --> 00:49:23,759
Madam, the Bishops are against you
and have no fear of you.

386
00:49:23,852 --> 00:49:26,521
They do not expect you to survive.

387
00:49:39,325 --> 00:49:41,364
My Lord ! The Queen !

388
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:06,679
Where have you been ?

389
00:50:11,146 --> 00:50:13,185
You were not at Court.

390
00:50:15,692 --> 00:50:17,731
Majesty, Monsieur de Foix.

391
00:50:17,819 --> 00:50:19,858
Mary of Guise, Ma'am,

392
00:50:19,946 --> 00:50:24,275
promises to make no further threat
against Your Majesty, but

393
00:50:24,367 --> 00:50:26,406
on one condition.

394
00:50:26,828 --> 00:50:28,867
What condition ?

395
00:50:29,581 --> 00:50:35,369
That Your Majesty considers the proposal
of her nephew the Duke of Anjou.

396
00:50:43,636 --> 00:50:47,503
The Duke is most eager
to meet Your Majesty.

397
00:50:47,598 --> 00:50:50,682
He has heard a great deal of your beauty.

398
00:50:51,476 --> 00:50:56,552
For the love of God, Madam, let not
the care of your diseased estate

399
00:50:56,648 --> 00:50:59,565
hang in the balance any longer.

400
00:50:59,651 --> 00:51:04,193
In marriage,
and in the production of an heir,

401
00:51:04,280 --> 00:51:06,990
Iies your only surety.

402
00:51:06,991 --> 00:51:09,991
The Duke is also most... handsome.

403
00:51:21,630 --> 00:51:23,669
Very well.

404
00:51:25,717 --> 00:51:27,424
Invite the Duke of Anjou.

405
00:51:28,929 --> 00:51:31,384
We shall see him in the flesh.

406
00:51:41,691 --> 00:51:43,730
Robert !

407
00:51:43,818 --> 00:51:48,526
The Duke will not take kindly
to a rival for his suit.

408
00:51:48,614 --> 00:51:52,445
He is a traitor,
and his father before him.

409
00:51:52,534 --> 00:51:57,444
Lord Robert's head
will end up on a spike,

410
00:51:57,539 --> 00:52:00,160
not on the pillow of a Queen.

411
00:52:12,929 --> 00:52:14,968
Must you leave ?

412
00:52:15,056 --> 00:52:17,926
I would not miss this for the world.

413
00:52:18,851 --> 00:52:22,978
Today I shall watch the fall
of that heretic girl.

414
00:52:26,733 --> 00:52:30,860
I have been placed here
as your sov...

415
00:52:36,660 --> 00:52:40,075
I am your sovereign.
I have been placed here...

416
00:52:42,790 --> 00:52:44,497
I...

417
00:52:44,584 --> 00:52:47,952
God has... God has placed me here...

418
00:52:48,045 --> 00:52:50,832
I am your anointed sovereign...

419
00:52:50,923 --> 00:52:54,374
I am your Queen...
And like my father I mean to rule.

420
00:52:54,468 --> 00:52:59,378
There is one thing higher than royalty,
my Lords, and that

421
00:53:00,390 --> 00:53:02,429
is religion.

422
00:53:03,727 --> 00:53:05,802
I pass this... I pass this Act of...

423
00:53:05,896 --> 00:53:07,805
I ask you to pa... I...

424
00:53:07,898 --> 00:53:10,982
I ask you to pass this Act of Uniformity.

425
00:53:11,067 --> 00:53:12,940
Not for myself. For my people.

426
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:17,319
They're my people...

427
00:53:17,949 --> 00:53:21,400
There is one God. We have
a common... There is one God.

428
00:53:23,037 --> 00:53:26,452
This is for my people.
My people are my care.

429
00:53:26,540 --> 00:53:28,579
The only care.

430
00:53:28,667 --> 00:53:32,118
My Lords, your votes are nothing
without my consent.

431
00:53:46,017 --> 00:53:52,055
If there is no uniformity
of religious belief here

432
00:53:52,148 --> 00:53:56,690
then there can only be fragmentation.

433
00:53:58,654 --> 00:54:00,693
Disputes and quarrels.

434
00:54:02,950 --> 00:54:08,952
Surely, my Lords, it is better
to have a single Church of England.

435
00:54:18,631 --> 00:54:21,465
A single Church of England !

436
00:54:21,551 --> 00:54:24,088
With a common prayer book.

437
00:54:24,178 --> 00:54:26,217
And... and a...

438
00:54:28,724 --> 00:54:31,760
And... a common purpose.

439
00:54:36,732 --> 00:54:39,851
I ask you to pass
this Act of Uniformity

440
00:54:39,943 --> 00:54:42,433
not... not for myself

441
00:54:44,489 --> 00:54:47,359
but for my people

442
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:52,531
who are my only care.

443
00:54:52,789 --> 00:54:54,828
Madam, by this Act,

444
00:54:55,291 --> 00:55:00,036
you force us to relinquish
our allegiance to the Holy Father.

445
00:55:00,129 --> 00:55:02,880
Hear, hear !

446
00:55:04,967 --> 00:55:07,457
How can I force you, Your Grace ?

447
00:55:07,553 --> 00:55:09,592
I am a woman.

448
00:55:12,599 --> 00:55:17,141
I have no desire
to make windows into men's souls.

449
00:55:19,231 --> 00:55:21,270
I simply ask

450
00:55:22,484 --> 00:55:24,523
can any man, in truth,

451
00:55:26,196 --> 00:55:28,437
serve two masters

452
00:55:28,531 --> 00:55:31,235
and be faithful to both ?

453
00:55:31,325 --> 00:55:33,531
Madam, this is heresy !

454
00:55:33,619 --> 00:55:36,323
No, Your Grace, this is

455
00:55:36,414 --> 00:55:38,453
common sense.

456
00:55:38,541 --> 00:55:41,625
Which is a most English virtue.

457
00:55:44,588 --> 00:55:47,458
Where is Gardiner ?
Where are the others ?

458
00:55:47,549 --> 00:55:49,043
Let us out !

459
00:55:49,134 --> 00:55:51,173
Open the door !

460
00:55:53,889 --> 00:55:56,593
This is Walsingham's doing.

461
00:55:56,933 --> 00:55:58,972
It is the devil's work.

462
00:55:59,060 --> 00:56:01,729
