518
01:02:07,034 --> 01:02:09,489
But do not despair.

519
01:02:09,579 --> 01:02:15,663
Was it not truly said
that the righteous shall inherit the earth ?

520
01:02:27,429 --> 01:02:29,468
Such piercing eyes !

521
01:02:29,556 --> 01:02:31,595
And very indiscreet !

522
01:03:04,339 --> 01:03:08,122
My true love has my heart

523
01:03:09,177 --> 01:03:11,216
and I have hers.

524
01:03:11,637 --> 01:03:13,676
My heart in me

525
01:03:13,764 --> 01:03:16,219
keeps her and me in one.

526
01:03:16,434 --> 01:03:21,095
My heart in her,
her thoughts and senses guide.

527
01:03:21,188 --> 01:03:23,429
She loves my heart

528
01:03:24,024 --> 01:03:26,811
for once it was her own.

529
01:03:27,903 --> 01:03:29,942
I cherish hers

530
01:03:31,448 --> 01:03:34,318
because in me it bides.

531
01:03:36,953 --> 01:03:39,408
My true love has my heart

532
01:03:39,497 --> 01:03:41,156
and I

533
01:03:41,249 --> 01:03:42,743
have hers.

534
01:03:42,834 --> 01:03:43,829
Marry me.

535
01:04:01,268 --> 01:04:03,307
Marry me.

536
01:04:05,730 --> 01:04:09,513
The Queen is very intimate
with Lord Robert, no ?

537
01:04:09,609 --> 01:04:14,021
With me she plays the shrew.
With him the lover ?

538
01:04:15,448 --> 01:04:19,231
Her life depends on the feelings
of my heart, yes ?

539
01:04:19,327 --> 01:04:23,027
She is a woman, Sire.

540
01:04:23,122 --> 01:04:26,371
They say one thing but mean another.

541
01:04:26,459 --> 01:04:28,534
No man can unlock their secrets.

542
01:04:28,627 --> 01:04:31,164
Unless they have

543
01:04:31,255 --> 01:04:33,792
a very big key !

544
01:04:36,093 --> 01:04:37,088
Yes !

545
01:04:37,177 --> 01:04:40,296
A very big key !

546
01:04:45,018 --> 01:04:47,057
On a night such as this

547
01:04:47,145 --> 01:04:49,184
could any woman say no ?

548
01:04:50,857 --> 01:04:52,896
On a night such as this

549
01:04:53,860 --> 01:04:55,899
could a Queen say no ?

550
01:04:56,779 --> 01:05:01,405
Does not a Queen sit under
the same stars as any other woman ?

551
01:05:05,079 --> 01:05:07,118
Monseigneur Alvaro !

552
01:05:07,831 --> 01:05:09,408
Monseigneur Alvaro !

553
01:05:09,499 --> 01:05:11,290
Tell me,

554
01:05:11,376 --> 01:05:15,503
as well as Ambassador,
are you not also a Bishop ?

555
01:05:16,965 --> 01:05:19,337
I am, my Lord.

556
01:05:19,425 --> 01:05:21,132
Then you can marry us !

557
01:05:23,054 --> 01:05:25,295
Marry you ?

558
01:05:26,307 --> 01:05:30,849
Perhaps he does not know enough
English to perform the ceremony !

559
01:05:30,936 --> 01:05:35,063
Alas, Madam, in this matter
I can be of no help to you.

560
01:05:38,944 --> 01:05:40,354
Madam !

561
01:05:42,864 --> 01:05:44,322
The Queen !

562
01:05:44,408 --> 01:05:46,566
- Protect the Queen !
- Help her !

563
01:05:47,702 --> 01:05:49,943
Quickly ! Call the Guard !

564
01:05:52,874 --> 01:05:55,411
The Queen ! The Queen !

565
01:05:55,501 --> 01:05:57,742
Look to the Queen !

566
01:06:09,431 --> 01:06:12,550
Isabel, see that the ladies are prepared.

567
01:06:12,643 --> 01:06:13,638
Isabel, go !

568
01:06:13,727 --> 01:06:15,766
Where were you, Sir Francis ?

569
01:06:15,854 --> 01:06:22,057
I only hope that Her Majesty may be
safely delivered from this present danger.

570
01:06:25,488 --> 01:06:27,527
Is the bedchamber ready ?

571
01:06:27,615 --> 01:06:30,022
Be calm, Madam. All is well.

572
01:06:30,118 --> 01:06:32,157
I am perfectly well.

573
01:06:32,787 --> 01:06:34,826
Please do not fuss.

574
01:06:39,251 --> 01:06:42,584
- No-one is to enter.
- Yes, Sir William.

575
01:06:44,465 --> 01:06:48,379
- Stay in here now, and watch.
- Yes, Sir Francis.

576
01:06:56,434 --> 01:06:58,177
Sorry, Lord Robert.

577
01:07:01,981 --> 01:07:03,225
I said no-one.

578
01:07:15,953 --> 01:07:17,862
My Lord,

579
01:07:17,955 --> 01:07:19,614
a word.

580
01:07:38,057 --> 01:07:40,512
To whose advantage was this ?

581
01:07:40,601 --> 01:07:42,474
De Foix ?

582
01:07:44,772 --> 01:07:46,396
No.

583
01:07:46,482 --> 01:07:48,521
Not with Anjou in play.

584
01:07:49,318 --> 01:07:51,725
Then some... madman ?

585
01:07:51,820 --> 01:07:54,773
There is always madness, Master Elyot.

586
01:07:54,865 --> 01:07:58,565
This was devised.
There is reason behind it.

587
01:07:59,160 --> 01:08:01,199
Then Alvaro

588
01:08:01,287 --> 01:08:03,575
for he has most cause.

589
01:08:03,665 --> 01:08:05,787
Yes, but he was present.

590
01:08:05,875 --> 01:08:08,116
He is too subtle for that.

591
01:08:09,170 --> 01:08:11,245
Would Norfolk ?

592
01:08:11,339 --> 01:08:15,418
He is not so subtle
and has even more cause.

593
01:08:15,509 --> 01:08:17,548
Indeed.

594
01:08:17,636 --> 01:08:19,295
So then

595
01:08:19,388 --> 01:08:22,472
he is not in league with the Spanish.

596
01:08:22,558 --> 01:08:25,048
Perhaps. Stay close to him.

597
01:08:25,143 --> 01:08:27,633
The Duke has some other game.

598
01:08:27,729 --> 01:08:30,266
I must find where he plays.

599
01:08:31,441 --> 01:08:35,983
I see it is true that the Queen
favours you above all others.

600
01:08:36,696 --> 01:08:40,823
But you have many enemies here.
Is it not so ?

601
01:08:40,908 --> 01:08:43,363
That is no concern of yours.

602
01:08:45,204 --> 01:08:47,243
It may be.

603
01:08:47,498 --> 01:08:51,875
If you would be prepared,
in secret, to renounce heresy

604
01:08:51,961 --> 01:08:54,368
and embrace the true faith,

605
01:08:54,463 --> 01:08:58,923
then you might find
many new and powerful friends

606
01:08:59,968 --> 01:09:01,794
and

607
01:09:02,304 --> 01:09:04,343
keep your Queen.

608
01:09:06,766 --> 01:09:09,766
You are most mistaken, Monseigneur,

609
01:09:09,853 --> 01:09:13,268
if you think
I might so easily be persuaded

610
01:09:13,356 --> 01:09:15,644
to act against my conscience,

611
01:09:15,733 --> 01:09:18,105
and my love.

612
01:09:18,819 --> 01:09:20,858
My Lord,

613
01:09:22,156 --> 01:09:24,943
what will a man not do for love ?

614
01:09:35,377 --> 01:09:38,876
Madam, if only you would heed my advice.

615
01:09:39,214 --> 01:09:44,800
I narrowly escaped with my life, sir.
I cannot now discuss marriage.

616
01:09:45,970 --> 01:09:50,512
Forgive me... the one
cannot be separated from the other.

617
01:09:50,600 --> 01:09:53,933
- Have I not told you ?
- Yes, and I am sick of it.

618
01:09:54,020 --> 01:09:57,602
This entire conversation is ill-timed.

619
01:09:58,190 --> 01:10:01,393
My patience, Sir William, is not infinite.

620
01:10:12,954 --> 01:10:16,785
It is a great joy to see
Your Majesty is not hurt.

621
01:10:16,875 --> 01:10:19,116
It was a terrible affair.

622
01:10:20,294 --> 01:10:24,421
The Duke would still
know the answer to his suit.

623
01:10:24,882 --> 01:10:29,045
You may tell the Duke
he shall have his answer shortly.

624
01:10:29,136 --> 01:10:31,461
Madam, the point is pressing !

625
01:10:33,140 --> 01:10:39,012
The Duke cannot love me so much if
he demands my answer so precipitously !

626
01:10:39,104 --> 01:10:43,101
Perhaps Her Majesty's heart
is already set upon another.

627
01:10:46,611 --> 01:10:51,438
Do not presume, monsieur,
to know the secrets of my heart.

628
01:10:53,910 --> 01:10:56,365
Monsieur de Foix may leave.

629
01:10:57,496 --> 01:10:59,535
Please, Excellency...

630
01:10:59,665 --> 01:11:02,120
Je vous prie de mes excuses.

631
01:11:03,460 --> 01:11:05,499
Secrets, Madam ?!

632
01:11:06,213 --> 01:11:08,252
You have no secrets !

633
01:11:08,340 --> 01:11:12,040
The world knows Lord Robert
visits your chambers and you

634
01:11:12,135 --> 01:11:14,174
fornicate with him !

635
01:11:14,262 --> 01:11:17,547
It's even said you already carry his child !

636
01:11:17,641 --> 01:11:22,551
Yes, Sir William, I live my life in the open !
I am surrounded by people !

637
01:11:22,645 --> 01:11:27,639
I do not understand how so bad
a judgment has been formed of me !

638
01:11:27,733 --> 01:11:29,690
Madam, you...

639
01:11:29,777 --> 01:11:31,568
You cannot marry Lord Robert !

640
01:11:37,451 --> 01:11:39,490
He is already married.

641
01:11:59,972 --> 01:12:02,427
Here comes our married man.

642
01:12:03,434 --> 01:12:06,103
Lord Dudley is not himself today.

643
01:12:06,604 --> 01:12:09,640
Lord Dudley's cup runneth over.

644
01:12:12,067 --> 01:12:15,815
Imagine being discovered
in another woman's bed !

645
01:12:15,904 --> 01:12:18,655
Aye, and that it to be his wife's !

646
01:12:29,667 --> 01:12:33,794
Lord Robert, we are amazed
you show your face at Court.

647
01:12:33,880 --> 01:12:35,919
The Queen !

648
01:13:09,997 --> 01:13:11,241
Spanish !

649
01:13:11,749 --> 01:13:13,124
Spanish !

650
01:13:15,169 --> 01:13:17,208
English pirate !

651
01:13:37,774 --> 01:13:39,813
English pirate !

652
01:13:39,901 --> 01:13:44,977
Is it not enough that English
pirates attack and rob our ships

653
01:13:45,072 --> 01:13:48,072
but we are to be made fools of
in this Court.

654
01:13:48,158 --> 01:13:53,318
The King, my master, has become
impatient for Your Grace to act.

655
01:13:55,165 --> 01:13:58,414
If you will not, then others may.

656
01:13:58,502 --> 01:14:02,499
You must reassure His Majesty
the time is close at hand.

657
01:14:02,589 --> 01:14:04,664
He must not act precipitously.

658
01:14:08,553 --> 01:14:12,550
- His Majesty has heard a rumour
- The world is filled with rumours.

659
01:14:12,640 --> 01:14:18,559
that Your Grace has made contact with
Mary of Scots to promote your ambitions.

660
01:14:18,646 --> 01:14:20,934
Even that you mean to marry her.

661
01:14:21,023 --> 01:14:23,560
Do you suppose me an idiot ?

662
01:14:23,651 --> 01:14:28,893
Your master is the most powerful man
in the world. I would not cross him.

663
01:14:35,120 --> 01:14:37,610
Will the Duke not come to dance ?

664
01:14:37,706 --> 01:14:42,616
Madam, His Grace is indisposed.
He has some pains of the stomach.

665
01:14:42,710 --> 01:14:44,334
Oh.

666
01:14:44,837 --> 01:14:47,292
I am very sorry for it.

667
01:14:54,096 --> 01:14:56,847
We wish to give the Duke this ring

668
01:14:58,016 --> 01:15:00,471
as a token of our love.

669
01:15:00,561 --> 01:15:03,016
- Madam...
- No.

670
01:15:03,105 --> 01:15:05,642
I shall give it to him myself.

671
01:15:05,732 --> 01:15:07,771
Madam, I should not...

672
01:15:07,859 --> 01:15:09,898
Sir William.

673
01:15:09,986 --> 01:15:11,812
Come along.

674
01:16:19,677 --> 01:16:21,716
What !

675
01:16:23,306 --> 01:16:25,345
What ?

676
01:16:25,766 --> 01:16:27,390
What, er... what !

677
01:16:31,772 --> 01:16:33,811
You stare, Madam.

678
01:16:37,694 --> 01:16:39,733
What is it ?

679
01:16:39,821 --> 01:16:41,860
Do you see

680
01:16:41,948 --> 01:16:44,617
something strange, perhaps ?

681
01:16:48,621 --> 01:16:51,491
You are wearing a dress, Your Grace.

682
01:16:52,208 --> 01:16:56,620
Oh ! Yes, I am wearing a dress.
Yes, yes, I am wearing a dress !

683
01:16:56,713 --> 01:16:59,916
I wear a dress like this,
my mother, and you.

684
01:17:00,007 --> 01:17:05,048
But I only dress like this when I'm alone,
in private, with my friends.

685
01:17:06,847 --> 01:17:08,886
Your Grace...

686
01:17:28,743 --> 01:17:31,992
Although my affection for you
is undiminished

687
01:17:32,079 --> 01:17:35,245
I have, after an agonising struggle,

688
01:17:35,333 --> 01:17:40,837
determined to sacrifice my own happiness
for the welfare of my people.

689
01:17:40,921 --> 01:17:42,249
My God !

690
01:17:49,179 --> 01:17:51,218
Madam, I will explain.

691
01:17:51,306 --> 01:17:54,390
There is no need, Excellency.

692
01:17:55,185 --> 01:17:58,055
I understand everything !

693
01:17:59,022 --> 01:18:00,397
Allez-vous-en, allez !

694
01:18:03,359 --> 01:18:05,398
Jouez ! Jouez !

695
01:18:08,739 --> 01:18:10,778
Up yours !

696
01:18:19,082 --> 01:18:21,833
Madam, is the, er... is the Duke...

697
01:18:21,918 --> 01:18:25,002
There will be no more talk of marriage.

698
01:18:43,689 --> 01:18:45,396
Lord Robert !

699
01:18:49,069 --> 01:18:51,108
Your Majesty ?

700
01:18:53,282 --> 01:18:55,488
Will you dance ?

701
01:18:57,911 --> 01:18:59,950
If it please you.

702
01:19:04,709 --> 01:19:06,748
Play a volta !

703
01:19:23,727 --> 01:19:25,849
Why will you not see me ?

704
01:19:38,992 --> 01:19:41,364
You must let me explain.

705
01:19:41,452 --> 01:19:44,121
Others will take advantage of this.

706
01:19:44,205 --> 01:19:48,036
You must not believe
what they tell you. They are jealous

707
01:19:48,125 --> 01:19:51,743
and envious,
because I am nothing to them

708
01:19:51,837 --> 01:19:54,374
and everything to you.

709
01:19:54,715 --> 01:19:56,754
Do you love her ?

710
01:20:00,971 --> 01:20:04,055
No, I love you.
I have always loved you.

711
01:20:04,140 --> 01:20:08,007
I was afraid of losing you
because I was not free !

712
01:20:08,103 --> 01:20:11,352
For God's sake,
you are still my Elizabeth !

713
01:20:13,858 --> 01:20:16,146
I am not your Elizabeth !

714
01:20:18,029 --> 01:20:20,068
I am no man's Elizabeth !

715
01:20:20,156 --> 01:20:23,192
And if you think to rule here
you are mistaken !

716
01:20:29,915 --> 01:20:31,990
I will have one mistress here

717
01:20:34,711 --> 01:20:36,750
and no master !

718
01:21:08,577 --> 01:21:12,740
It matters nothing to me.
I can live without her

719
01:21:13,039 --> 01:21:15,197
most happily.

720
01:21:15,291 --> 01:21:17,864
Better than I could live with her.

721
01:21:20,088 --> 01:21:24,880
I have no need of her love.
Have I not suffered enough already

722
01:21:24,967 --> 01:21:27,374
for loving her and showing it ?

723
01:21:27,470 --> 01:21:29,509
I envy you, my Lord.

724
01:21:29,889 --> 01:21:32,379
To love a woman so deeply.

725
01:21:32,474 --> 01:21:36,886
Monseigneur... envy no man for that.

726
01:21:39,314 --> 01:21:41,721
Such love is hateful.

727
01:21:41,817 --> 01:21:46,312
It tears the soul apart. Envy a man
who has never known such love.

728
01:21:46,404 --> 01:21:50,650
Perhaps there may still be a way
to reclaim her affections.

729
01:21:50,742 --> 01:21:52,319
Why should I want to ?

730
01:21:52,410 --> 01:21:54,283
And to save her life.

731
01:21:54,370 --> 01:21:57,074
- You jest with me.
- No, I do not.

732
01:21:57,164 --> 01:22:02,750
For she will be dead soon enough,
perhaps even at Norfolk's hand,

733
01:22:02,836 --> 01:22:04,875
if you do not help her.

734
01:22:06,173 --> 01:22:08,130
How can I help her ?

735
01:22:10,219 --> 01:22:12,258
She will not even see me.

736
01:22:19,227 --> 01:22:21,717
His Holiness has issued the Bull.

737
01:22:21,813 --> 01:22:27,317
It deprives Elizabeth, pretended Queen
of England, servant of wickedness,

738
01:22:27,401 --> 01:22:29,440
of her throne,

739
01:22:29,529 --> 01:22:35,068
and declares that her subjects
are absolved of their allegiance to her.

740
01:22:37,494 --> 01:22:40,578
His Holiness also decrees that any man

741
01:22:40,664 --> 01:22:44,531
who should undertake her assassination

742
01:22:44,626 --> 01:22:48,753
will be welcomed by angels
into the Kingdom of Heaven.

743
01:22:49,881 --> 01:22:54,589
Give these letters of blessing
and hope to our friends in England.

744
01:22:58,431 --> 01:23:03,804
THE COAST OF ENGLAND

745
01:23:43,140 --> 01:23:45,179
Your Grace.

746
01:23:45,350 --> 01:23:47,389
Monseigneur.

747
01:23:56,569 --> 01:23:58,608
And Thomas Elyot.

748
01:24:00,865 --> 01:24:03,320
You serve your master well, Elyot.

749
01:24:04,243 --> 01:24:06,282
As well as I can, in truth.

750
01:24:06,704 --> 01:24:08,743
I mean your real master.

751
01:24:10,374 --> 01:24:12,413
What's this ?

752
01:24:12,668 --> 01:24:14,707
What master ?

753
01:24:14,795 --> 01:24:16,372
Walsingham.

754
01:24:16,463 --> 01:24:19,547
The priest is mistaken, my Lord.

755
01:24:19,633 --> 01:24:23,132
I am Your Grace's servant,
as God is my witness.

756
01:25:07,887 --> 01:25:10,971
- Isabel...
- Sshh, don't fuss.

757
01:25:15,519 --> 01:25:20,429
You should not try them on, lsabel.
They are the Queen's dresses.

758
01:25:20,524 --> 01:25:22,563
Why not ?

759
01:26:14,993 --> 01:26:17,032
You're my secret.

760
01:26:17,120 --> 01:26:19,159
I am Queen, aren't I ?

761
01:26:19,747 --> 01:26:21,786
Say you're mine.

762
01:26:24,210 --> 01:26:26,249
You're my Elizabeth.

763
01:26:27,129 --> 01:26:29,168
Say you're my Elizabeth.

764
01:26:29,465 --> 01:26:31,504
I am your Elizabeth.

765
01:26:38,765 --> 01:26:40,840
I am your Queen !

766
01:26:49,525 --> 01:26:51,564
Ssh... !

767
01:26:53,779 --> 01:26:55,818
Sshh... !

768
01:27:18,136 --> 01:27:20,175
Kat ?

769
01:27:22,473 --> 01:27:24,512
Kat !

770
01:27:37,863 --> 01:27:40,270
Kat ?

771
01:27:48,289 --> 01:27:50,328
Who are you ?

772
01:27:51,960 --> 01:27:54,533
You will declare yourself to me.

773
01:27:59,634 --> 01:28:01,092
Madam !

774
01:28:02,470 --> 01:28:06,799
Something has happened !
You must come quickly !

775
01:28:06,932 --> 01:28:08,971
Who was with her ?

776
01:28:09,059 --> 01:28:13,637
One of the guards found her.
He says he saw Lord Robert leave...

777
01:28:13,730 --> 01:28:15,521
No, Madam, no.

778
01:28:15,607 --> 01:28:18,180
The dress was poisoned.

779
01:28:19,027 --> 01:28:21,600
Uncover her.

780
01:28:24,991 --> 01:28:27,660
No... ! That dress was a gift

781
01:28:28,703 --> 01:28:30,742
for me.

782
01:28:31,664 --> 01:28:33,703
French silk.

783
01:28:36,252 --> 01:28:39,336
SCOTLAND

784
01:28:51,975 --> 01:28:54,014
Vite ! Vite !

785
01:29:13,120 --> 01:29:15,159
Sir Francis,

786
01:29:16,206 --> 01:29:19,824
you and I must be honest with each other.

787
01:29:24,714 --> 01:29:26,753
Your Queen is weak.

788
01:29:27,884 --> 01:29:29,923
She has no army,

789
01:29:30,011 --> 01:29:33,047
no friends. Only...

790
01:29:33,139 --> 01:29:34,763
Comment dit-on... ?

791
01:29:35,641 --> 01:29:37,514
- Enemies.
- Enemies.

792
01:29:37,602 --> 01:29:39,393
Mm-hm.

793
01:29:39,478 --> 01:29:41,517
What terms can she propose ?

794
01:29:42,022 --> 01:29:44,809
Madam, Her Majesty was, I believe,

795
01:29:44,900 --> 01:29:48,564
too hasty at rejecting
the Duke's proposal of marriage.

796
01:29:49,113 --> 01:29:51,817
But how can I marry such a woman ?
Huh ?

797
01:29:51,907 --> 01:29:53,733
She is frigid !

798
01:29:55,118 --> 01:29:58,367
Yes ! They even say she is really a man !

799
01:29:59,539 --> 01:30:02,705
Go to bed. Leave me with this.

800
01:30:04,961 --> 01:30:06,918
Forgive my nephew.

801
01:30:07,005 --> 01:30:09,412
He speaks when he should not.

802
01:30:09,507 --> 01:30:11,546
He is terrible.

803
01:30:23,270 --> 01:30:25,345
Ne fais pas I'idiot, Henri.

804
01:30:32,821 --> 01:30:36,865
I hear you are a wise man, Sir Francis,

805
01:30:36,950 --> 01:30:39,737
and a creature of the world

806
01:30:39,827 --> 01:30:41,369
Iike me.

807
01:30:48,002 --> 01:30:50,041
Yes.

808
01:30:52,673 --> 01:30:54,712
I have no illusions.

809
01:30:58,053 --> 01:31:01,137
I know it is only a matter of time

810
01:31:01,723 --> 01:31:04,593
before my Queen is overthrown.

811
01:31:09,022 --> 01:31:12,106
Her Majesty rules with the heart,

812
01:31:14,402 --> 01:31:16,477
not with the head.

813
01:31:16,571 --> 01:31:18,610
I understand.

814
01:31:19,281 --> 01:31:22,780
It is hard for a woman to forget her heart.

815
01:31:26,455 --> 01:31:28,494
But, er...

816
01:31:29,208 --> 01:31:31,247
what of you,

817
01:31:32,586 --> 01:31:34,625
Walsingham ?

818
01:31:36,506 --> 01:31:41,132
A wise man would be careful
not to put himself in the way of harm.

819
01:31:43,930 --> 01:31:46,966
And how would a wise man do that ?

820
01:31:47,725 --> 01:31:51,010
He would, as I said, change allegiance.

821
01:31:52,688 --> 01:31:54,727
Allegiance ?

822
01:31:59,028 --> 01:32:01,103
There are but two choices.

823
01:32:02,156 --> 01:32:06,235
He would get into bed
with either Spain or France.

824
01:32:09,454 --> 01:32:11,493
And whose bed

825
01:32:11,581 --> 01:32:13,407
would you prefer ?

826
01:32:31,100 --> 01:32:34,184
Your Majesty, may I speak with you ?

827
01:32:34,269 --> 01:32:36,142
In private.

828
01:32:46,072 --> 01:32:48,111
Speak.

829
01:32:49,200 --> 01:32:51,869
You are in the greatest danger.

830
01:32:52,328 --> 01:32:54,783
You must believe me.

831
01:32:56,082 --> 01:32:58,121
But you have a friend.

832
01:32:58,209 --> 01:33:01,328
Someone who can guarantee your safety

833
01:33:02,588 --> 01:33:04,710
and your throne.

834
01:33:07,968 --> 01:33:10,007
A friend ?

835
01:33:12,681 --> 01:33:14,720
The King of Spain.

836
01:33:18,228 --> 01:33:20,267
Leave us.

837
01:33:31,198 --> 01:33:33,486
How would he guarantee it ?

838
01:33:37,079 --> 01:33:39,118
He would marry you.

839
01:33:42,084 --> 01:33:45,748
Only to make an alliance. Nothing more.

840
01:33:46,838 --> 01:33:49,163
He would not expect to...

841
01:33:50,258 --> 01:33:52,297
He would live in Spain.

842
01:33:54,721 --> 01:33:57,425
Why do you do this, Robert ?

843
01:33:57,515 --> 01:34:00,302
Because I love you.

844
01:34:00,393 --> 01:34:05,434
And though you will not see me,
I am the only one who would care for you.

845
01:34:05,523 --> 01:34:09,852
You love me so much
you would have me be your whore ?

846
01:34:16,658 --> 01:34:19,409
For God's sake, I do this for us.

847
01:34:19,494 --> 01:34:22,411
I ask you to save some part of us !

848
01:34:22,497 --> 01:34:28,285
Lord Robert, you may make whores of my
Ladies but you shall not make one of me.

849
01:34:37,345 --> 01:34:39,384
Your Majesty.

850
01:34:46,520 --> 01:34:49,935
Elizabeth is a witch !

851
01:34:50,899 --> 01:34:52,938
A witch !

852
01:34:53,819 --> 01:34:56,356
And her servant is the devil !

853
01:35:12,169 --> 01:35:14,208
Get out ! Get out !

854
01:35:16,256 --> 01:35:18,711
Of course I shall deny it.

855
01:35:19,259 --> 01:35:24,882
Your Majesty must publicly dissociate
herself from this most bloody act.

856
01:35:24,973 --> 01:35:27,012
I never ordered it.

857
01:35:30,061 --> 01:35:32,516
Of course, Madam, of course.

858
01:35:32,605 --> 01:35:37,065
You must also make conciliatory gestures
towards the Spanish.

859
01:35:37,151 --> 01:35:41,444
Your dependence upon their goodwill
is greater than ever.

860
01:35:41,530 --> 01:35:45,029
- I must...
- The word "must" is not used to princes.

861
01:35:49,455 --> 01:35:54,615
I have followed your advice
in all the affairs of my kingdom, but

862
01:35:54,710 --> 01:36:00,000
your policies would make England
nothing but part of France or Spain.

863
01:36:02,342 --> 01:36:05,924
From this moment
I am going to follow my own opinion.

864
01:36:06,012 --> 01:36:09,261
Forgive me, Madam,
but you are only a woman.

865
01:36:09,349 --> 01:36:15,517
I may be a woman, Sir William, but
if I choose I have the heart of a man !

866
01:36:18,357 --> 01:36:20,729
I am my father's daughter.

867
01:36:21,568 --> 01:36:23,975
I am not afraid of anything.

868
01:36:25,322 --> 01:36:27,148
I...

869
01:36:29,451 --> 01:36:34,611
I deeply regret, Madam,
if I have caused you such offence

870
01:36:35,415 --> 01:36:39,910
though God knows
all my advice has only ever been

871
01:36:42,547 --> 01:36:45,168
to secure Your Majesty's throne.

872
01:36:45,591 --> 01:36:47,832
And I am grateful for it.

873
01:36:53,974 --> 01:36:58,434
I have decided to create you
Lord Burghley,

874
01:36:58,520 --> 01:37:01,604
so you may enjoy your retirement
in greater ease.

875
01:37:01,690 --> 01:37:05,817
- Madam...
- That will be all, Lord Burghley.

876
01:37:13,243 --> 01:37:14,653
Majesty...

877
01:37:43,104 --> 01:37:45,143
Madam, if I may ?

878
01:37:46,441 --> 01:37:50,189
A prince should never flinch
from being blamed

879
01:37:50,278 --> 01:37:55,734
for acts of ruthlessness which are
necessary for safeguarding the State

880
01:37:55,825 --> 01:37:57,864
and their own person.

881
01:37:59,453 --> 01:38:04,909
You must take these things so much
to heart that you do not fear to strike

882
01:38:06,501 --> 01:38:09,585
even the very nearest that you have

883
01:38:10,797 --> 01:38:13,252
if they be implicated.

884
01:38:15,427 --> 01:38:17,466
It has been made known to me

885
01:38:17,554 --> 01:38:22,346
there is a priest abroad in the land,
carrying letters from Rome

886
01:38:22,433 --> 01:38:25,303
to those who mean to harm you.

887
01:38:28,481 --> 01:38:31,565
Norfolk's power in Court is growing.

888
01:38:31,650 --> 01:38:34,319
It is said that he and his foreign allies

889
01:38:34,403 --> 01:38:37,439
are raising an army
to outnumber your own.

890
01:38:37,531 --> 01:38:40,152
IfYour Majesty does not act soon

891
01:38:40,242 --> 01:38:42,281
then he will.

892
01:38:45,330 --> 01:38:49,244
Find the priest,
and those who harbour him.

893
01:38:50,543 --> 01:38:54,243
Right, search every room !
You two, upstairs !

894
01:39:05,224 --> 01:39:07,382
Where is Lord Arundel ?

895
01:39:10,938 --> 01:39:12,977
He's not here, sir.

896
01:39:23,032 --> 01:39:25,653
Do you know where your father is ?

897
01:40:12,288 --> 01:40:15,372
You were carrying letters from the Pope.

898
01:40:15,457 --> 01:40:18,126
To whom were you told to give them ?

899
01:40:29,137 --> 01:40:31,176
Tell me,

900
01:40:31,389 --> 01:40:33,630
what is God to you ?

901
01:40:35,893 --> 01:40:38,134
Has He abandoned you ?

902
01:40:38,688 --> 01:40:44,274
Is He such a worldly God that
He must play at politics and conspiracy ?

903
01:40:45,694 --> 01:40:47,935
Is He not divine ?

904
01:40:49,364 --> 01:40:54,109
Tell me the truth, as if you were
face to face with Him now.

905
01:40:58,248 --> 01:41:00,703
I am a patient man, Father.

906
01:41:13,471 --> 01:41:15,130
Sussex,

907
01:41:15,222 --> 01:41:16,965
Gardiner,

908
01:41:17,057 --> 01:41:18,800
Arundel.

909
01:41:18,892 --> 01:41:21,561
A man will confess to anything

910
01:41:22,479 --> 01:41:24,804
under torture.

911
01:41:27,692 --> 01:41:31,191
And Lord Robert Dudley,
Earl of Leicester.

912
01:41:50,464 --> 01:41:56,050
Madam, this document was also found
among the priest's possessions.

913
01:41:56,136 --> 01:42:01,046
From His Holiness the Pope
to His Grace the Duke of Norfolk.

914
01:42:04,019 --> 01:42:10,222
"To legitimise your claim to the throne
of England, His Holiness proposes

915
01:42:10,316 --> 01:42:14,609
"Your Grace should take as your bride
Mary, Queen of Scots,

916
01:42:14,695 --> 01:42:16,734
and overthrow Elizabeth..."

917
01:42:16,822 --> 01:42:20,071
The illegitimate and heretical whore

918
01:42:20,159 --> 01:42:22,696
who now sits upon the throne.

919
01:42:22,786 --> 01:42:29,583
All Norfolk need do is sign this paper,
and treason will have been committed.

920
01:42:31,962 --> 01:42:34,417
Then let him sign it.

921
01:42:36,299 --> 01:42:38,754
And let it all be done.

922
01:42:58,529 --> 01:43:00,568
In the future,

923
01:43:01,657 --> 01:43:05,072
when England is safe again and faithful,

924
01:43:05,160 --> 01:43:09,987
they will thank me for this act
and forget the manner of it.

925
01:43:11,791 --> 01:43:13,830
Is it not true ?

926
01:43:41,945 --> 01:43:44,518
Deliver this most carefully.

927
01:47:26,658 --> 01:47:29,148
What is the meaning of this ?

928
01:47:29,244 --> 01:47:33,905
Your Grace is arrested.
You must go with these men to the Tower.

929
01:47:33,999 --> 01:47:36,916
I must do nothing by your orders.
I am Norfolk.

930
01:47:37,001 --> 01:47:38,874
You were Norfolk.

931
01:47:40,964 --> 01:47:43,419
The dead have no titles.

932
01:47:52,099 --> 01:47:55,847
You were the most powerful man
in England

933
01:47:55,936 --> 01:47:59,139
and could have been greater still

934
01:47:59,231 --> 01:48:02,267
but you had not the courage to be loyal.

935
01:48:04,569 --> 01:48:08,317
Only the conviction of your own vanity.

936
01:48:08,406 --> 01:48:13,779
I think, Walsingham, a man's courage
is in the manner of his death.

937
01:48:15,121 --> 01:48:18,205
I am content to die for my beliefs.

938
01:48:19,876 --> 01:48:21,915
So cut off my head

939
01:48:22,712 --> 01:48:25,167
and make me a martyr.

940
01:48:25,881 --> 01:48:28,965
The people will always remember it.

941
01:48:29,968 --> 01:48:31,794
No...

942
01:48:33,347 --> 01:48:35,588
They will forget.

943
01:48:37,476 --> 01:48:39,515
Your Majesty

944
01:48:40,020 --> 01:48:42,059
knows that

945
01:48:42,188 --> 01:48:44,857
I did it only for my faith.

946
01:48:46,192 --> 01:48:48,231
Nothing more.

947
01:48:50,988 --> 01:48:54,487
All your many kindnesses
are remembered.

948
01:49:02,041 --> 01:49:06,168
You must not think
we care not for your children.

949
01:49:07,504 --> 01:49:10,789
Your Majesty is merciful and forgiving.

950
01:49:30,192 --> 01:49:32,647
What kept you, Walsingham ?

951
01:49:34,571 --> 01:49:36,610
I have been waiting.

952
01:49:50,086 --> 01:49:52,125
Your Majesty...

953
01:49:52,213 --> 01:49:54,786
They are all gone to the Tower.

954
01:49:54,882 --> 01:49:56,921
Your friends.

955
01:50:03,891 --> 01:50:05,930
Tell me,

956
01:50:08,437 --> 01:50:11,521
how should I serve thee, Robert ?

957
01:50:19,072 --> 01:50:21,313
My course is run.

958
01:50:24,035 --> 01:50:26,490
Just tell me why.

959
01:50:28,915 --> 01:50:30,954
Why ?

960
01:50:33,044 --> 01:50:35,083
Madam,

961
01:50:39,008 --> 01:50:42,590
is it not plain enough to you ?

962
01:50:45,180 --> 01:50:48,050
It is no easy thing to be loved

963
01:50:48,558 --> 01:50:50,799
by the Queen.

964
01:50:56,024 --> 01:50:59,108
It would corrupt the soul of any man.

965
01:51:02,363 --> 01:51:05,233
Now, for God's sake, kill me.

966
01:51:09,453 --> 01:51:11,492
No...

967
01:51:12,831 --> 01:51:15,535
I think rather to let you live.

968
01:51:15,626 --> 01:51:20,371
Madam, that is not wise.
Lord Robert has committed treason.

969
01:51:20,464 --> 01:51:25,624
- He must be made example of.
- And I will make an example of him.

970
01:51:31,307 --> 01:51:33,762
He shall be kept alive

971
01:51:35,853 --> 01:51:38,308
to always remind me

972
01:51:39,732 --> 01:51:42,816
of how close I came to danger.

973
01:52:44,001 --> 01:52:46,871
I have rid England of her enemies.

974
01:52:47,922 --> 01:52:50,377
What do I do now ?

975
01:52:50,674 --> 01:52:52,915
Am I to be made of stone ?

976
01:52:54,928 --> 01:52:57,383
Must I be touched by nothing ?

977
01:52:57,472 --> 01:53:00,009
Aye, Madam, to reign supreme.

978
01:53:02,102 --> 01:53:07,855
All men need something greater than
themselves to look up to and worship.

979
01:53:17,033 --> 01:53:20,318
They must be able to touch the divine

980
01:53:22,580 --> 01:53:24,619
here on earth.

981
01:53:32,422 --> 01:53:35,506
She had such power over men's hearts.

982
01:53:41,639 --> 01:53:43,880
They died for her.

983
01:53:44,892 --> 01:53:48,177
They have found nothing to replace her.

984
01:55:21,943 --> 01:55:24,564
You will be damned for this !

985
01:55:25,530 --> 01:55:27,356
Tonight I think I die.

986
01:55:28,532 --> 01:55:29,776
Speak up !

987
01:56:10,864 --> 01:56:12,903
Kat...

988
01:56:19,289 --> 01:56:21,958
I have become a virgin.

989
01:57:24,810 --> 01:57:27,265
Observe, Lord Burghley.

990
01:57:30,357 --> 01:57:32,598
I am married

991
01:57:33,026 --> 01:57:35,267
to England.

992
01:58:35,099 --> 01:58:38,018
ELIZABETH REIGNED
FOR ANOTHER 40 YEARS

993
01:58:38,769 --> 01:58:41,896
WALSINGHAM REMAINED HER
MOST LOYAL COUNSELLOR

994
01:58:42,523 --> 01:58:45,650
SHE REMAINED UNMARRIED AND NEVER
RECEIVED DUDLEY IN PRIVATE AGAIN

995
01:58:46,402 --> 01:58:49,655
ON HER DEATHBED SHE
WHISPERED HIS NAME

996
01:58:50,405 --> 01:58:54,492
WHEN SHE DIED ENGLAND WAS THE
MOST POWERFUL COUNTRY OF EUROPE

997
01:58:55,243 --> 01:58:58,871
HER REIGN WAS CALLED
THE GOLDEN AGE

998
01:59:03,918 --> 01:59:08,338
THE VIRGIN QUEEN

999
